, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Hungerford","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Hungerford (Berkshire), from Old English <i>hungor</i> ‘hunger’, here probably denoting unproductive land, + <i>ford</i>. This surname has been established in Ireland since the 17th century."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":70,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":79,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Walter de Hungerford was born in 1145, in Hungerford, Somerset, England, his father, Walter Everard de Hungerford, II, was 35 and his mother, Elizabeth de Heytesbury, was 33. He married Emmeline FitzWarin of Whittington in 1159. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1231, in Wiltshire, England, at the age of 86, and was buried in Wales."},"et":{"1145?–1231":"1145–1231","1145–1231":"1145–1231","1145–1200":"1145–1200","1160–1186":"1160–1186","1185–Male":"1185–Surnud","1110–1200":"1110–1200","1112–Female":"1112–Surnud","1215":"1215","1159":"1159","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1112":"1112","1145":"1145","1145?":"1145","1231":"1231","1110":"1110","1186":"1186","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","Hungerford, England":"Hungerford, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Wales":"Wales","Heytesbury, Wiltshire, England":"Heytesbury, Wiltshire, England","Hungerford, Somerset, England":"Hungerford, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"1145?–1231":"1145–1231","1145–1231":"1145–1231","1145–1200":"1145–1200","1160–1186":"1160–1186","1185–Male":"1185–Kuollut","1110–1200":"1110–1200","1112–Female":"1112–Kuollut","1215":"1215","1159":"1159","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1112":"1112","1145":"1145","1145?":"1145","1231":"1231","1110":"1110","1186":"1186","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","Hungerford, England":"Hungerford, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Wales":"Wales","Heytesbury, Wiltshire, England":"Heytesbury, Wiltshire, England","Hungerford, Somerset, England":"Hungerford, Somerset, England"},"fr":{"1145?–1231":"1145–1231","1145–1231":"1145–12